snippet.textDisplay:
I loved the first water drop. Can't believe you made it right in! That deformation was astounding!

Some ideas to consider for future shows:

Make a sand pendulum: https://www.enchantedforestshop.com/products/the-magical-sand-pendulum
Test parachutes on the atlas stone: Can you make a parachute that will cause it to fall slowly?
More fun with parachutes: Cover the sand with hula hoops as targets. All the boys at the top, drop thousands of these little green paratroopers and get points for where they land: https://www.aliexpress.com/wholesale?SearchText=toy+parachute+soldier
Earthquake Detectors: See if you can partner with a Geoscience team in your location to install some earthquake detectors in the sand. Drop big things and see what type of signature they produce on the detectors. https://www.ga.gov.au/scientific-topics/community-safety/earthquake
Nail in fence posts? I wonder if you could drive fence posts in to the sand with the stone or thor hammer? Drive metal fence posts in to other things? Worlds-biggest hammer and nail?

snippet.textDisplay: Okay to clarify what it did to the plant paint is basically the same thing that would happen to a human body if they were in a body of water while an explosion happened under water because the water has nowhere to go but passed the human body and because the human body is taking up space as the explosion of water is reaching the human body it would literally liquify the human in the water because that water has to occupy the space where the human is well in this case when the ball hits the water the water has to go somewhere so the force of the water hitting the side of the barrel is the equivalent of an explosion happening within the barrel as the stone Atlas Stone impact the water that water has to go somewhere so it is literally stretching the barrel trying to go the only way that it can, out... so when the atlas Stone impact the top half of the water it is stretching that barrel trying to go out but it can't go out so now it splashes up but in that same moment it's then also hitting the bottom half of the barrel and again the water is trying to Splash in an outward fashion trying to escape out of the barrel and it to finally reaches a point where I can't stretch Barrel any further and moves in an upward fashion that's why you see not one but two splashes of water being released from the barrel at impact
